Reasoning: The paper discusses the representation of words and categories, which is a common topic in natural language processing and computational linguistics (cs.CL). The proposed category representation also has applications in knowledge representation and understanding, which falls under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the mathematical definition and classification of conceptual systems and communication, which could be considered as topics in social informatics (cs.SI) and information theory (cs.IT).
